  "text": "Chronic inflammation affects myeloid cell development from the initial production of multipotent progenitors in the BM through their differentiation and recruitment to sites of inflammation. Colitis models show disrupted hematopoiesis, including alterations in hematopoietic stem and progenitor cell (HSPC) proliferation and myeloid/lymphoid differentiation capacity, and shifts in the relative abundance of specific progenitor cells in the BM [CITATION_1] . Diabetes causes systemic chronic inflammation (37), and T2D was recently shown to induce widespread changes to the BM stem cell niche that diminish numbers of early hematopoietic progenitors and deregulate miRNAs induced during the macrophage inflammatory response [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . However, the full extent of the effect of diabetes on hematopoiesis is unknown.",
